===Etymology 1===
From Middle English ''[[bere]]'', from Old English ''[[bera]]''; related to Old English ''[[brun]]'' (brown).

====Noun====
{{sb|bear|bears}}

#<!--DefA--> A large carnivorous mammal, related to the dog and racoon, having shaggy hair, a very small tail, and flat feet.
#<!--DefB--> {{colloquial}} An animal that resembles a bear, such as a [[koala]], [[panda]], or [[sloth]].  <!-- FWIW, pandas are actually in the family Ursidae -->
#<!--DefC--> {{finance}} An [[investor]] who sells in anticipation of falling prices.
#<!--DefD--> {{colloquial}} A problem that is very difficult to solve.
# {{slang}} A large hairy man, especially one who is [[gay]].

